# Test Project Structure Rules

- All test scenarios (specs) MUST reside in `tests/e2e`.
- Page Object classes MUST reside in `tests/pages`.
- Shared helper functions and utility modules MUST reside in `tests/helpers`.
- Test data, constants, and mock data MUST reside in `tests/fixtures`.
- If a test file (`.spec.ts`) exceeds 200 lines, you MUST extract logic into Page Objects or helpers.
- Use meaningful names for files and directories that reflect their purpose.
